ObservationText: Weather is absolutely beautiful. A little breezy, not too sunny, just perfect! Was worried it would be cold!
The clouds are looking extra nice… I know I tend to be observant of clouds but these ones really stand out to me. I like how it seems like a sheet covering the world.
The geese or ducks… whatever animal is in the picture… I am a little scared of them. I’m hesitant to walk close so I keep going in the grass to avoid any unwanted contact.
Two of them are strayed off from the rest… remind me of me and my best friend from home
The butterfly in the picture was so pretty. I saw some before but couldn’t get a picture fast enough. I had “pet” butterflies when I was little! They were monarchs… so cute.
A lot of bikers are out. People often run in pairs. I don’t think I could successfully hold a conversation while running so I am impressed every time I see that occur.

The water is really still. Nothing is out on it. It’s quite peaceful. I find it interesting how most things remind me of other things from home. Example: we have a small lake in my neighborhood where I used to visit often with my friends. This one is way bigger and is significantly more calm. Ours always had animals flying around and swimming in it.
There aren’t many flowers… something I am missing. Maybe I haven’t gotten far enough yet, but the flowers I see are all the same. Pretty nonetheless.
I am from a small rural town, so I really love having a view of buildings like this.
Was fascinated by how many (geese? ducks?) there are. They tend to stay together in groups and waddle around as one.
If you look very, very closely at one of the flowers, there is a pretty, white butterfly!
People in graduation cap and gowns are taking pictures with the Rhett statue
There’s a guy on his phone; he’s wearing glasses and looking down like I am right now as I type:)
I see people having fun sitting on a bench, and laughing and swaying to music behind the BU beach
“Can you take two minutes for mental health” yard sign from SHS
Skateboarding people practicing with their own rail while jamming to music
These cars are going really fast under the overhead bridge and are so so loud!
There’s rowing teams on the river that are practicing back and forth. Pretty sure they’re BU teams!
Sound of rowing speaker phone
So many people are running with and without dogs
I see a rollerblader!
Woah!! A bicyclist that almost HIT me – she rang her bell last last second
Random wooden board by the river with a bunch of circles carved out that I have no clue about.
Graffiti on the side of the bridge
I almost fell!
Painted meter box with a frog and other animals on the side of it. So cool!
Sailing boats parked and numbered at the sailing pavilion.
I’m taking a picture of a woman far away taking a picture of the water from a bridge.
There was a crazy loud pigeon noise under the bridge that scared me
There’s squirrels chasing each other on a tree

OOPS I went West instead of East from the starting point, so now I’m heading East. My friend made sure to mock me haha. But now I know where the sailing place and pigeons are under the bridge at least:)
I just saw that one of the sailing boats almost ‘fell’ while turning. Maybe it’s on purpose, who knows?
I see a couple running with their baby in a stroller.
There was a man on a cool bike with a basket in the front, and sunglasses on.
A guy is trying to read a book by the water but is actually looking at his phone. So very distracted.
Outdoor gym!
Took some water and sun pictures by the cool floating place for people to sit (don’t know what it’s called– maybe a boardwalk?)
Geese apparently move their necks in a rapid back and forth motion while eating! I hadn’t really thought about it.
White flowers are blooming on this shrub like it’s spring.
Damn! A man on a motorized unicycle was on his phone. No way, I’ve never seen that before. Had a helmet on though.
A dude was whistling loudly on his walk.
Fall colors are coming in!! Woohoo! Just the entire park is pretty
I see a car with blinking lights, parked on the side of the road
There’s two girls jogging and chatting about their day.
I keep stepping on lots of acorns as I walk.
Lots of Canada Geese in the area, some of them are grooming their feathers or lying down, others look like they’re maybe foraging for food
They (geese) were surprisingly unafraid of people: I passed right next to some of themand they didn’t even budge
Lots of trees lining the walkway
Most of them (trees) are still green, although I did notice a few that were starting to be tinged yellow
I think it’ll look even prettier once the trees fully change color
Couple of unique trees along the path too
A couple of super short, stubby trees that had really wide-ranging branches and leaves
Also a lot of willow trees, especially closer to the river
Some of them had little plaques saying what type of tree they were, which was pretty interesting
Lots of people outside, probably because the weather is so nice
Most of them are jogging or biking
I saw one person skating using some kind of pole looking things
Two people are sitting on a bench, they look like they’re working or studying
Some people sitting on benches looking like they’re just admiring the view
Someone walking somewhere looking like they’re in a hurry and in business casual dress. Maybe they’re late to work?
2 kayakers with sunhats on, looking like they’re enjoying the sunny weather
A few people (teams?) rowing on the Charles River. They’re chanting/singing some kind of song
The city skyline against the Charles River looks really beautiful
Especially cool because to my right (towards BU), it’s all rustic, older buildings, but to my left (across the river) there’s a bunch of modern, skyscraper type buildings
Cool combination of old and new
Super cute little black and brown corgi running alongside their owner who’s on a bike
Also saw a man with his dog on a bench. He was trying to get the leash on his dog but the dog just kept trying to move around and lick his face instead (adorable!)
2 dogs walking together. One looked like an identical copy of the other one, just a lot smaller
A few colorful/abstract murals on the side of a bridge and on the columns of the bridge
Makes an industrial structure look a bit more beautiful with a pop of color
Weather is really sunny, the sunlight hitting the Charles River makes for a really nice view and a pretty contrast with the surrounding greenery
Saw a wooden dock with a lone red lawn chair
Fairly quiet, even though there’s quite a few people around; really peaceful/serene atmosphere, especially combined with the crisp fall air
Saw a few uprooted trees, including a huge willow
A lone red lawn chair looking out over the Charles River.
A beautiful combination of a cityscape and nature.
A tree tinged yellow, just starting to change color.

At the very beginning of my walk, I noticed a dog running around full of joy as its owner called him over. The dog seemed to be enjoying the sunshine as it was showing off its “zoomies” to everyone passing by.
A lot of people walking
Even more running
Super sunny and warm conditions
People sitting down admiring nature
Dogs running around seem happy
Landscape view of the city from the esplanade looks like a photograph
Everything looks still-despite all the movement
Feels like “a call before the storm”
People seem to be enjoying the sunny day in October
My assumption is that people are trying to get some sun and nature in during their lunch breaks from work
A lot of geese around
Feels like a summer day
Trees are still their summer green color
barely any at autumn colors apparent
Doesn’t look as if nature is in October
River is extremely calm
Some leaves slowly falling to the ground
The smell outside was very clean to me, I felt at home almost- forgetting that I was thousands of miles away
Walking also made me take a step back and realize where I was
It was almost a surreal feeling just taking a step outside of campus and experiencing what is outside of school and everything
I saw the city over the still ocean, enclosed by the trees next to the path.
There was a red crane looming over the city skyline.
There were a lot of runners enjoying a morning run and bikers riding past.
The ocean was on one side while cars whizzed by on the other.
There were a lot of geese along the path and swimming peacefully in the water.
I took in the smell of fresh air and caught whiffs of gasoline when cars and trucks passed by.
There was a biker who was stretching their quads while riding a bike. He had very good balance!
I loved the bright, bold colors of the art painted under the bridges.
A man was wearing a helmet with large, black horns protruding out from the top.
I heard women speaking another language while running with each other.
I passed a playground, and there were little kids swinging on a swing set.
The sun was shining through trees, making a cool pattern with the shade and light on the path.
The buildings across the ocean are captured by the trees and bushes. The clear, blue sky creates a beautiful background.
The art on the side of the bridge is painted with a variety of colors and shapes that make the wall pop.
Smell of freshly cut grass in the air
The constant roar of cars passing by
Rowboats and coaches shouting far off in the Charles River
Squirrels munching on a pile of nuts
Slight bloat from the food I probably shouldn’t have eaten right before the walk
Geese walking around like they own the place
Strong sea breeze near the river
Someone walking his dog while on roller skates
Very detailed graffiti of skulls underneath bridge
Someone biking past me carrying a big skeleton on his back
Person wearing neon LED equipment on a motorized unicycle

A blurry photo of the person on the unicycle, not very clear since I had to quickly pull out my phone before they sped off at what must have been 20 miles per hour. They were turning and controlling very smoothly, so I would assume they are an experienced driver.
Right from the start I noticed lots of bikers, runners, and walkers
I could hear the fast cars on the highway, but for some reason I started to forget I was in the city (probably due to the benches, grass, and trees present)
In the distance I could also hear nearby planes flying in the sky
I saw leaves falling to the ground and the trees in different colors!!!!!
Everyone kept to themselves, some would nod and some would not
I really loved how there were views of cambridge (I think) from across the water
The water was so blue and still (it had ripples but they were quiet)
There were large geese everywhere in one particular area of the trail, some came really close to me but still minded their own business, I did not see any other organisms
Every once and a while I could hear birds chirping, but it was faint and quiet (sometimes hard to hear due to the highway)
These Geese were everywhere! It was a little scary, because they came so close, but they did not mean any harm and were just snooping in the grass.
This view was seen about halfway through my walk. It was so pretty to see the water, but also the other side of the river.
Lots of joggers
Sound of the cars going by on Storrow
Windy
Fog, can’t see the tops of buildings in the distance
Group of people picking up litter on the esplanade
So many geese
Lots of fallen leaves
Cute baby in a stroller
Lots of cute dogs going on walks
Not a ton of animals besides geese and a couple squirrels
Dark clouds, looks like it’s going to rain soon
This tree stood out to me because it is the only tree around that started changing colors for fall. It made me excited for when all of the trees change colors.
Three girls laying on a picnic blanket in the grass with their bikes parked next to them
A woman with fuschia colored pants skates passed me with roller blades (I see her when I turn around going the other direction)
Hardly any traffic on the road to the right side of the esplanade
The river looks peaceful and the water is still
In the distance there are red and white sailboats beyond the bridge
A lot of runners run past me as I walk down the trail, people on bikes ring their bells to warn me they are riding through
About 5 minutes into the walk I smelled Cod almost as if someone was frying fish sticks
The leaves on the trees were mainly green and now yellow or orange; there was very little wind and everything seemed still and calm
I walked by a dock; About 5 different couples were sitting on it looking out into the water
A man was fishing on the bridge and another man was crouched down near the rocks fishing
I looked up into the sky and saw three helicopters in the air. They didn’t seem like they were moving, just floating in space
The foundation of the bridge I went under had paintings of different birds (one looked like a goose, the other looked like an eagle??)
I walked by two willow trees near each other: one looked half alive and half dead and the other was lying horizontally on the ground
Pictured: The two willow trees I passed; The one on the left appears half healthy half dead and the one on the right has fallen over.
Under the bridge, the pillar has an eagle drawn on it and the one in front of it had a goose (this caught my eye - do these birds mean something?)

I first notice the piles and piles of acorns on the sides of the overpass, tumbling and cracking as bikes ride over them or as I step on them. They roll around, hard shells making noises against the concrete.
All along the trail people are weaving around each other, bikes and scooters passing those of us walking.
I see a mural and art with birds, butterflies, flowers, patterns, beautiful in a space that is rusted and supposed to be ugly because it’s a water/electricity box.
A hoard of geese ahead, splitting slowly to either side of the pass as people move through them
I walked out to the dock, found an emptied bottle of alcohol and geese poop, discarded food and trash from the time kids spent out there during late nights.
The dock swayed its weight which each step I took outward.
Looking at the “desire paths” next to the paved walkway, showing where people habitually walk to avoid others or move on dirt rather than concrete.
Bikes and scooters quickly whiz around geese and people at a dangerous speed
Straight ahead on the path before it curves, an opening of the guardrail opens straight to the highway, if you were to keep walking straight you would walk right onto Storrow drive.
I walk over to a fallen tree in the water, that instead is split in two directions, hanging together by a small branch across the middle
Another strip of mural, narrowing the path to be right along the water and highway
I see the exit off Storrow drive I always take, looking at it from a completely new angle
Noticing people's litter, little pink feathers and trash like crushed cups, cigarettes, straws, package mailers, shake shack bags.
I notice people have graffiti’d over the murals, but that it’s been painted over to preserve the original art
I notice a squirrel perched behind on a bench, peering over anxiously
Goose looks elegant for a moment, slowly blinking its eyes in the sunlight while resting
I wonder how the geese and ducks get onto the dock from the water as i see a group of them swimming over
A crack in the mural below Storrow drive where a plant has poked through. I loved it’s positioning in the lighter blue circle.
The exit I would take off of Storrow Drive from growing up in the Boston area. It was very interesting to see it from the opposite side.
Here is a fallen tree I saw that fell in different directions, but had this bridge-like part of it connecting each side.
Started at 3:32
Noticed a lot of bikers and runners
It was a nice temperature to go for a walk so it was very relaxing
I had some good music going and started to listen to the sounds of my surroundings on top of that
I was very annoyed at the road noise
All of these runners are making me feel like I should be running
They are now reminding me of why I don’t like running
I miss biking at home
Ended at 4:03
Below is my photo. I have no idea what it is, or what it is used for, which is why I chose it. I spent longer than I should have analyzing it, but I came to no real conclusion about its purpose.
What does snow look like falling onto the river?
This looks like San Francisco Bay a little with the bridges in the background
Somebody was in a hammock, and I immediately texted my parents asking them to bring my hammock family weekend
Little brown weiner dog!
Cute little dock: The water was really black around it, almost like oil. It might have just been the shadow though
A bunch of grazing/sitting geese: no one sits on the benches near them
Note: The time isn’t 30 minutes because I stopped to look at things a lot on the way there, and then didn’t really stop on the way back.
Many bikers and groups of runners
Geese along the walking trail (weren’t afraid of humans??)
People sitting along the benches of the esplanade
Mostly chatting with one another
Enjoying the hot and nice weather
So many bunnies! They were everywhere along the grass and by the path
So many trees and greenery
Water was surprisingly disgusting/murky
Sailers out on the Charles River
Super windy, scooping water out of their boats!!
I didn’t realize MIT was just across the river, so when I turned back from the esplanade, I decided to go on an adventure
I made it to MIT! I rested in the shade in the middle of the main lawn and people watched MIT students come in and out of class
MIT students are surprisingly normal… overheard a conversation about quantum physics and then decided it was time for me to head back!!
October 8th 2:16 pm is when I began the walk. ( Walked for 20 minutes first way and 17 minutes the other way)
The first thing I notice are the rustling leaves being thrown around by the wind.
I also see an array of joggers and runners running up and down the path resembling the different positions, directions and speeds of life different people are operating at all times.
A lot of cyclists either on a Blue Bike or their own cycles zooming past the runners which to me put into emphasis the modern reliance on machinery that most people have.
Charles River seems like the one big mirror holding the view in place
The rampant noise of the city of Boston is a vivid noise as I walk along the path and now turn around to walk back.
The sharp glare of a bunny straight into my eyes as we both try to break each other down, almost as if the bunny is trying to figure out whether I can perceive it.
The Old Lady’s two Dogs walking in unison , showing that friendship and strong bond that dogs have within family and a sense of loyalty which they possess in their behavior.
The sudden stark contrast between the smell of tobacco and a flower garden acts as the multicultural city of Boston and how there is a diverse community amongst us.

The contrasting minds, body languages, vibes and people in general walking past each other for the first and last times in their lives probably each thinking about something different is what emphasizes why different kinds of minds are so interesting.

A Large group of bikers wearing similar clothing came along. They don't seem to be extremely impressed by the view into the water when they all stop there to take a break. They must be from here, accustomed to the pretty view.
A harmony of the water and wind, mixed with traffic from the nearby streets. Perfectly reflects the connection between city and nature in this park.
It's not crowded here at all. I’m suppressed essentially everyone spends their time in the busy crowded city, and not in this peaceful park just minutes away.
I need to come here more often
A moment overseeing the river and skyline, surrounded by nature from the park.
Sitting down on bench near the road and overpass
Slightly windy and cold
2 geese are in the little open space, one goose is standing on one leg? Can they do that
a man is walking on the muddy area right next to the walking pavement- there seems to be a hollow already throughout the path
humans create their own pathways in nature- negative environmental effects- grass and soil deteriorating
a boy walking with it appears to be his grandfather- small glances between each other
the geese fly away low to the ground squawking - that would’ve definitely hit someone
a man electric scooters past
a girl on the bench near me is working on school work
for the runners going past, the outfits range from fleeces and sweatpants to a sports bra and biker shorts as well as the pace
two twenty something girls just started their run with an “omg I can’t believe he did that”
someone in a teal unicycle just wobbled by
the runners and i glance at each other, no communication
the playground is empty on a tuesday morning/midday
the trees are sporadically placed with many different kinds
did not know about this overpass before and now I think it seems a good study spot
cloudy day and a slight chill seems perfect for a run along the charles river
It’s really starting to feel like fall now, which I very much appreciate and enjoy since fall is my favorite season
It's my favorite type of weather!
people are out walking, running, or riding bikes on this beautiful October day
people in boats rowing along the Charles River
Autumnal colored leaves scattered on path and actively falling off trees
I like crunching them [leaves] as I walk, very satisfying
Brings me back to my childhood
Some trees are starting to turn yellow and orange, but most still green
Cute little daisies lining the path
Makes me happy! [daisies]
Giant yellow mushroom that looks like it came out of a fantasy novel (pictured below)
It smells like fall!!
Smell of grass and woodsy scent
Carries especially on the crisp autumn air
More animals than I expected!
Lots of geese that proved to be sort of problematic (pictured and explained below)
Squirrels chasing each other up trees
Ducks!!! I love ducks, especially mallard ducks like the ones I saw
The scenery of the Charles River with the skyline behind it is beautiful, especially from this one bridge I came across (pictured below)
The giant mushroom that looks like it came straight out of a fairytale, but the picture doesn’t do a good job of conveying just how massive this was.

Okay funny story about this picture. As I was walking, there was a lady in front of me also walking. Out of nowhere these two geese swoop down directly in front of her and cut her off. It looked like a helicopter landing: leaves went everywhere, dust flew up in the air, and they cleared out their area of impact. The poor lady had to jump back so the geese didn’t hit her, and then they proceeded to stand right in our way and only moved after a good 10 second staring contest.
A picture from the secluded bridge, you can see the leaves drifting in the water and right underneath the bridge there were ducks swimming (mallard ducks, my favorite).
